        <p class="article-meta">Last Updated On: <strong>June 26, 2022</strong></p>
        <img id="article-image" src="images/article5.jpg" alt="Responsibilities of a Good Quran Teacher - Dar Arqam Online Quran Classes" class="article-image">
        
        <div id="article-content" class="article-content">
            <p>A good Quran teacher plays a crucial role in shaping how students understand and connect with the Quran. Their responsibilities go beyond simple recitation—they provide clear guidance, adapt to different learning styles, and foster a deep love for the Quran. Effective Quran teaching ensures students learn with proper pronunciation, comprehension, and reverence.</p>
            <p>A responsible Quran teacher ensures correct Tajweed, adapts lessons to student needs, and creates a respectful, motivating learning environment. Regular revision, constructive feedback, and consistent practice are also essential for steady progress. By fulfilling these responsibilities, a Quran teacher can create a transformative and enriching learning experience for students worldwide.</p>

