            <h3 id="proper-tajweed">1. Teaching the Quran with Proper Tajweed and Pronunciation</h3>
            <p>One of the most critical responsibilities of a Quran tutor is ensuring students recite with proper Tajweed and correct pronunciation. Since the Quran must be read as it was revealed, tutors must:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Teach each Tajweed rule step by step.</li>
                <li>Focus on letter articulation and intonation.</li>
                <li>Guide students through practical exercises to correct common errors.</li>
                <li>Provide continuous correction to build accuracy and confidence.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This ensures that learners can recite the Quran beautifully, preserving its sacredness.</p>

            <h3 id="adapting-teaching">2. Adapting Teaching to Student Learning Levels</h3>
            <p>Every student learns at a different pace, so a skilled tutor adjusts their teaching approach accordingly. For example:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Simplifying lessons for beginners.</li>
                <li>Introducing challenges for advanced students.</li>
                <li>Using visual aids and interactive methods for young learners.</li>
                <li>Encouraging discussions and reflections for teenagers and adults.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>By being flexible, tutors help students feel comfortable, motivated, and confident in their learning journey.</p>

            <h3 id="love-for-quran">3. Instilling a Love for the Quran</h3>
            <p>A great tutor not only teaches but also inspires a deep love for the Quran. This can be done by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Sharing inspiring stories and lessons from the Quran.</li>
                <li>Highlighting the spiritual and personal benefits of memorization and recitation.</li>
                <li>Encouraging students to reflect on the meanings of verses.</li>
                <li>Providing positive reinforcement and celebrating milestones.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>When students develop a strong emotional and spiritual connection to the Quran, they are more likely to stay committed to their studies.</p>

            <!-- Journey Button -->
